      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "EYE WISH (7) was very good in the Gold Bracelet series, chasing a top filly for second in the heats before finishing only 3.6m away when third in the final. Two from two at this circuit and distance and should be race fit third up. STAR TO FALL (10) resumes after winning four of six starts as a juvenile including a heat and a semi of the Vicbred Super Series before coming from the back row for a midfield finish in the final when last seen in November. Won the only time she attempted this circuit and distance and will be ready to go off two trial wins. APPLAUDING (2) was last seen when fifth in the Group 1 Breeders Challenge final at Menangle in October but has been readied with two trial placings. Draws well and her lone win came at this circuit and distance. CAPTURE OUR HEART NZ (6) also comes through the Gold Bracelet series where she placed in the heats and she usually races well here.",
